-- MISC DESC
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_GHILLIEWRAP_DESC"] = "Lines the outside of the armor with camoflauge materials to help blend into natural surroundings."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_STRENGTHENED_DESC"] = "Binds the armor with additional reinforcement materials to increase durability."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_PADDED_DESC"] = "Extra padding sewn into the armor to help absorb impacts.\n\nIncreases Explosive Damage Threshold."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_DENSE_DESC"] = "Denser materials are used in the construction of this armor.\n\nGreatly Increases Explosive Damage Threshold."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POCKETED_DESC"] = "Provides some extra space by attaching small pouches to the inside of the armor.\n\nIncreases Carry Weight."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_DEEP_POCKETED_DESC"] = "Provides a lot of extra space by attaching large pouches to the inside of the armor.\n\nGreatly Increases Carry Weight."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_LEAD_LINED_DESC"] = "Air-tight lead lining prevents radioactive particles from penetrating the armor.\n\nIncreases Radiation Resistance."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_LIGHT_DESC"] = "High quality cooling and lightweight materials for the inner lining of armor.\n\nReduces weight and improves mobility without sacrificing protection."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_ULTRALIGHT_DESC"] = "Premium cooling and lightweight materials for the inner lining of armor.\n\nGreatly Reduces weight and improves mobility without sacrificing protection."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_SHEER_DESC"] = "Simplfies the inner lining without sacrificing protection.\n\nReduces Save Weight Cost."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_STEALTHLINING_DESC"] = "This lining embeds the armor with a portable stealth field lining\n\nThe Stealth Field activates when you are crouched, making it very difficult for you to be seen."

-- Power Armor
-- Misc Mods
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_SERVO_DESC"] = "All it took to optimized these servos was a few more grease points and some more hinges. As a result it you gives you a higher total carry weight."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_TESLA_DESC"] = "These shiny new coils and capacitors provide superior protection against energy attacks. The Tesla Attraction Coil Rods disperse a large percentage of directed energy attacks."

-- Leg Mods
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_CALIBRATED_DESC"] = "A slight recalibration of the shock struts should allow you to carry more. Just be careful not to set them too high..."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_OVERRIDE_DESC"] = "Overriding and overdriving. These bad boys should make you faster at the cost of your range of motion and future maintenance."

-- Arm Mods
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_REBAR_DESC"] = "Behold the latest word in big badda boom hardware. At least for raiders. These are really just extra rebar you stuck on your fists. At least it should hurt."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_HYDRAULIC_DESC"] = "Replacing the acuators and increasing the PSI should give you more 'oomph' for your swings. Should be more than enough to knock the head off of anyone who crosses you."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_OPTIMIZED_DESC"] = "A few calibration tweaks and some new parts should make moving these arms far more natural to use."

-- Torso Mods
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_EMERGENCY_PROTOCOL_DESC"] = "Used by pre-war soldiers to protect them from incoming artillery fire by rushing adrenaline through their body. Whenever you are at or below 25% HP this advanced system will send a stream of chemicals throughout your body to help you with your flight from combat."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_CORE_ASSEMBLY_DESC"] = "A popular upgrade for soldier pre-war. This feat of engineering provides higher AP at the cost of making the suit wear out faster."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_BLOOD_CLEANSER_DESC"] = "WHile still technically experimental still, the wasteland has more than prooved its usefulness. Reduces the chance of addiction to a chem by 25%. Quite popular among bandits."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_JETPACK_DESC"] = "First used in the Sea of Tranquility by the brave men and women of the U.S. Army. Now this extremely rare and powerful old world marvel is gonna make sure nobody can keep you grounded."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_STEALTH_DESC"] = "Researched pre-war but constructed post-war, this piece of technology has made quite in advancement in war fighting weapons."

-- Helmet Mods
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_RAD_SCRUBBER_DESC"] = "Using borrowed technology from Vault-Tec and expanding the O2 tanks make this thing quite handy in the irritated post-war America."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_SENSOR_ARRAY_DESC"] = "These weird sensors seem to flatten the image that is in focus, making its silhouette easy to distinguish, but obscuring the details."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_DATABASE_DESC"] = "An internal database still connected to a pre-war net. Quite a feat in science and engineering if you think about it."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_RECON_SENSOR_DESC"] = "The sensors have been finely tuned to distinguish pieces of scrap and junk from one another. Allowing you to find items in containers more often."

-- Material
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_HARDENED_PLATE_DESC"] = "This armor plating has undergone a special chemical hardening process. All around improving your suits resistances at the cost of making it much heavier."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_EMP_PLATE_DESC"] = "Using rare and expensive Dissipative Polyethylene Shielding has made EMP based weapons deal significantly less damage to your armor. Just don't expect it to stop a bullet." 
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_PRISM_PLATE_DESC"] = "Made using Adaptive Lens and sloping in different directions to help deflect energy attacks away from the user. May also redirect the sun to burn Radroaches."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_TITANIUM_PLATE_DESC"] = "Made using heavy duty metal plates that are then chemically infused with titanium to strengthen them. It will provide betetr protection against ballistic and melee attacks."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_LEAD_PLATE_DESC"] = "Heavy as hell but sure beats the alternative. With this much protection you'd think your about to enter a nuclear crater."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_EXPLOSIVE_PLATE_DESC"] = "With enough padding and explosive resistant material you can probably tank any missiles shot at you. Or atleast a few."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMOR_VAULTSTEEL_PLATE_DESC"] = "The pinnacle of protection in the post-apocalypse. With this much protection you'd think your about to take on an army. Just be careful not scratch the paint."

-- Power Armor Frames
-- Materials
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMORFRAME_MATERIAL_REINFORCED_DESC"] = "Reinforced with steel plates and advanced materials. The extra plating should keep suit from breaking down more at the cost of weighing a bit more."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMORFRAME_MATERIAL_VAULTSTEEL_PLATE_DESC"] = "Reinforced with Vault Steel Plates. Created post-war, for a post-apocalyptic world."

-- Generators
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMORFRAME_GEN_OVERCLOCK_DESC"] = "An overclocked TX-28 Generator. The normal Fusion pack is already powerful enough, but with a little extra juice you can squeeze more out of it. Just don't expect it to last as long."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMORFRAME_GEN_PLASMA_DESC"] = "An XL-10 Plasma Generator. These things were only for the best of the best pre-war. While they are hard to come by you sure can't beat the power these bring. It also reduces Energy Ammo weight by 40%."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMORFRAME_GEN_NUCLEAR_DESC"] = "Developed after the battle of Anchorage and put in service during the Gobi Campaign. The TX-78 Nuclear Generator produced more power then previous power packs. While it has some practical issues they are easy to over look in the post-apocalypse."
lang["#MOD_ARMOR_POWERARMORFRAME_GEN_HELLFIRE_DESC"] = "Created by some of greatest minds post-war, it has been specially enhanced and is vastly superior to most other power packs. Despite the XE-04 Hellfire Generator being just a prototype it has more than enough juice to keep America's elite fighting forces going. It also reduces Energy Ammo weight by 40%."

